==English==

===Etymology===
Late {{L.}} ''deviatus'', p.p. of ''[[deviare]]'', from the phrase ''de via''.

===Pronunciation===
*Verb:
**dē'vēāt, /ˈdiːvieɪt/, /<tt>"di:vieIt</tt>/
*Noun:
**dē'vēət, /ˈdiːviət/, /<tt>"di:vi@t</tt>/

===Intransitive verb===
{{en-verb|deviat|ing}}

# To go off course from; to change course; to change plans.
#:''He's '''deviating''' from the course.  Follow him!''
# To be outside of or part from some norm; to stray.

====Synonyms====
*(''change course''): [[swerve]], [[veer]]
*(''stray''): [[stray]], [[wander]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}
# One who deviates; a [[deviant]].

===Related terms===
*[[deviant]]
*[[deviation]]

